<subSubSection pageId="37" pageNumber="38" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1437,152,2018]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,343,1351,1377]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Etymology:</emphasis>
After Giovanni Onore, who kindly sent me specimens for study and is a great activist on the study of Latin American scarabaeoids. Gender neutral.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="37" pageNumber="38" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1437,152,2018]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,361,1431,1457]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Distribution:</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[371,471,1432,1458]" name="Ecuador" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, northern 
<collectingCountry box="[594,651,1432,1458]" name="Peru" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Peru</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry box="[717,813,1432,1458]" name="Panama" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Panama</collectingCountry>
, comprising the Arid 
<collectingCountry box="[1079,1176,1432,1458]" name="Ecuador" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
and Tumbes-Piura in the Northwerstern South American dominion, and Eastern Central America, in the Mesoamerican dominion, both in the Caribbean subregion. Cited from coastal 
<collectingCountry box="[765,885,1512,1538]" name="Venezuela" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Ferreira, A. M. R. M. &amp; Galileo, M. H. M." box="[930,1235,1512,1538]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" pagination="3 - 70" refId="ref48083" refString="Ferreira, A. M. R. M. &amp; Galileo, M. H. M. (1993) Revisao taxonomica do genero Pedaridium Harold, 1868 (Coleoptera, Scarabaeidae, Scarabaeinae, Coprini). Iheringia, Serie Zoologia, 74, 3 - 70." type="journal article" year="1993">Ferreira &amp; Galileo (1993)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="37" pageNumber="38" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1437,152,2018]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,321,1551,1577]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Remarks:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vaz-De-Mello" authorityYear="2008" box="[331,471,1552,1577]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Onoreidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[331,471,1552,1577]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Onoreidium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has several apomorphies, such as, the unusual clypeal form, uniquely developed lateral mesotibial and metatibial tooth, thick pseudoflagellum, and convex head. It appears to be the sister genus of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vaz-De-Mello" authorityYear="2008" box="[261,416,1632,1657]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Pereiraidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[261,416,1632,1657]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Pereiraidium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, sharing with that genus the modified anterior tarsi in both males and females, strong tooth in claws, and same general head shape. This clade appears to be related to the 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Trichillidium-Bradypodidium</emphasis>
clade (absence of ventral protibial scale-like setae, widely emarginated clypeus, strong lateral pronotal carina, and relative apical position of protibial tooth); however, it is not clear if that is a sister-group relationship, or if they form different grades of a paraphyletic group in relation to the remaining genera of 
<taxonomicName authority="Vaz-De-Mello, 2008" authorityName="Vaz-De-Mello" authorityYear="2008" box="[1319,1436,1792,1818]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="10" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subTribe" status="new subtribe" subTribe="Scatimina">Scatimina</taxonomicName>
with fused abdominal sternites.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="37.[151,1437,152,2018]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[198,367,1871,1897]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Composition:</emphasis>
Besides the 
<typeStatus box="[517,567,1872,1898]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">type</typeStatus>
species, the new genus contains 
<taxonomicName authority="(Arrow, 1931)" authorityName="Vaz-De-Mello" authorityYear="2008" baseAuthorityName="Vaz-De-Mello" baseAuthorityYear="2008" box="[956,1248,1872,1898]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Onoreidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ohausi" status="new combination">
<emphasis box="[956,1070,1872,1897]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">O. ohausi</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Arrow, G. J." box="[1086,1239,1872,1898]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" pagination="609 - 611" refId="ref47149" refString="Arrow, G. J. (1931) The coleopterous genus Trichillum (Copridae), with a key to the species. The Annals and Magazine of Natural History, Series 10, 8, 609 - 611." type="journal article" year="1931">Arrow, 1931</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="37" pageNumber="38" rank="species">new combination</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(described as 
<taxonomicName box="[376,498,1912,1937]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Trichillum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[376,498,1912,1937]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Trichillum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), 
<taxonomicName authority="(Ferreira &amp; Galileo, 1993)" authorityName="Vaz-De-Mello" authorityYear="2008" baseAuthorityName=": Ferreira &amp; Galileo" baseAuthorityYear="2008" box="[525,1104,1912,1938]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Onoreidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="howdeni" status="new combination">
<emphasis box="[525,774,1912,1937]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Onoreidium howdeni</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Ferreira, A. M. R. M. &amp; Galileo, M. H. M." box="[792,1095,1912,1938]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" pagination="3 - 70" refId="ref48083" refString="Ferreira, A. M. R. M. &amp; Galileo, M. H. M. (1993) Revisao taxonomica do genero Pedaridium Harold, 1868 (Coleoptera, Scarabaeidae, Scarabaeinae, Coprini). Iheringia, Serie Zoologia, 74, 3 - 70." type="journal article" year="1993">Ferreira &amp; Galileo, 1993</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1118,1335,1911,1937]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1118,1335,1911,1937]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" rank="species">new combination</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Howden &amp; Young, 1981)" authorityName="Vaz-De-Mello" authorityYear="2008" baseAuthorityName=": Howden &amp; Young" baseAuthorityYear="2008" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Onoreidium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bottimeri" status="new combination">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Onoreidium bottimeri</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Howden, H. F. &amp; Young, O. P." box="[354,656,1952,1978]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" pagination="1 - 173" refId="ref48888" refString="Howden, H. F. &amp; Young, O. P. (1981) Panamanian Scarabaeinae: taxonomy, distribution, and habits (Coleoptera, Scarabaeidae). Contributions of the American Entomological Institute, 18 (1), 1 - 173." type="journal article" year="1981">Howden &amp; Young, 1981</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[680,897,1951,1977]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[680,897,1951,1977]" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" rank="species">new combination</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(described as 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Harold" authorityYear="1868" box="[1075,1213,1952,1977]" class="Insecta" family="Scarabaeidae" genus="Pedaridium" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="37" pageNumber="38" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1075,1213,1952,1977]" italics="true" pageId="37" pageNumber="38">Pedaridium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); and at least two new species are under study.
</paragraph>
